{
 "id": "cdm_lactobacillaceae",
 "name": "CDM \u2014 chemically defined medium for Lactobacillaceae",
 "category": "laboratory",
 "organism_scope": "Lactobacillaceae",
 "aerobic": false,
 "description": "Chemically defined medium that supports growth of the whole Lactobacillaceae family. Glucose plus acetate and citrate, all 20 amino acids, the nucleobase/nucleoside set (uracil, guanine, adenine, xanthine, inosine, orotate, thymidine) and the B-vitamins. Exchange constraints as published in Table 2 of Ardalani et al. (mSystems 2024). Inorganic ions and water are opened, as they were left unconstrained in the paper's FBA setup.",
 "namespace": "bigg",
 "provenance": {
  "source_type": "Published (GEM paper)",
  "citation": "Ardalani O., Phaneuf P.V., Mohite O.S., Nielsen L.K. Pangenome reconstruction of Lactobacillaceae metabolism predicts species-specific metabolic traits. mSystems 9(7):e00156-24 (2024), Table 2.",
  "doi": "10.1128/msystems.00156-24",
  "url": "https://doi.org/10.1128/msystems.00156-24",
  "notes": "Ids are given in the pre-2018 BiGG convention (EX_glc_D_e, EX_arg_L_e), matching LactoPanGEM. Four labels in the published table disagreed with their BiGG id and are corrected here to the id: EX_ura_e is uracil (not uridine), EX_gua_e is guanine (not guanosine), EX_ade_e is adenine (not adenosine), and EX_nac_e is nicotinate/niacin (not N-acetyl-D-glucosamine, which is EX_acgam_e). The ids are unchanged."
 },
